00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:02,300
- Come here. 
 - Over here.

17
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,360
- Pay the bill if you are late. 
 - Yeah.

18
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,419
I'm not late.

19
00:02:11,419 --> 00:02:13,959
We are all single. Why bother being so petty?

20
00:02:13,959 --> 00:02:15,080
- Yeah. 
 - Come, come.

21
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,340
- Shall we toast? 
 - Here.

22
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:18,940
Cheers.

23
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:27,720
It's still the same bunch of friends.

24
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:32,879
Sadly, next year, not all of us will be here.

25
00:02:32,879 --> 00:02:35,120
Yu Tu will work at an investment bank.

26
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:37,120
It's a complicated circle. 
  (T/N: world of sensual pleasures) 

27
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,440
He won't be as pure and innocent as we are.

28
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:44,159
Which means we will always be one man short.

29
00:02:44,159 --> 00:02:46,720
Maybe we'll have Old Guan.

30
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,799
What's with Guan Zai?

31
00:02:47,799 --> 00:02:49,040
Sister-in-law is asking for a divorce.

32
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,400
No way!

33
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,919
They're such a loving couple.

34
00:02:51,919 --> 00:02:54,520
She gave up a high-paying job in America just to be with him.

35
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,919
Why is it not possible?

36
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:57,760
His model task is already demanding.

37
00:02:57,760 --> 00:03:00,719
If Yu Tu pulls out of the research project, he must do it all alone.

38
00:03:00,719 --> 00:03:03,120
He's been working overtime and hardly has time to see anyone.

39
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,760
Of course Sister-in-law would be angry.

40
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:06,439
What about the others?

41
00:03:06,439 --> 00:03:09,520
Didn't they hire two new hands before I took leave?

42
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,400
What's the point of having new hands?

43
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,079
No one knows it better than you.

44
00:03:13,079 --> 00:03:15,050
Besides, you know how fussy Old Guan is.

45
00:03:15,050 --> 00:03:17,320
One screw-up or two, and he'll dismiss you.

46
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,520
Stop it, you guys.

47
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:21,520
Chief Guan even showed off a loving breakfast to me.

48
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:26,999
Yeah, Big Meng. You said this out of sheer envy as a bachelor.

49
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,600
Can you at least aim first?

50
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:32,899
- Let me see. 
 - Okay, let's dig in.

51
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,860
Just this one.

52
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:41,220
Yu Tu, I recently read a paper

53
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:44,060
that gave me some inspiration. I want to discuss it with you.

54
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:46,600
Remember to keep it secret. Don't divulge our technology.

55
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:48,680
I'm talking to him about foreign technology. What's wrong?

56
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:52,580
What can I talk about with him in the future? The real estate market in Lujiazui?

57
00:03:52,580 --> 00:03:54,819
Insolent!

58
00:03:54,819 --> 00:03:58,520
You dare talk about the real estate market of Lujiazui?

59
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,420
You're becoming bolder and bolder!

60
00:04:00,420 --> 00:04:02,400
Fine, I'm not worthy.

61
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,620
Okay, let's eat.

62
00:04:25,980 --> 00:04:29,760
   

63
00:04:39,719 --> 00:04:41,879
 We don't come here very often. Let's sing Karaoke. 

64
00:04:41,879 --> 00:04:44,680
 - Yeah. 
 - Count me out. I don't know any new songs. 

65
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:45,839
 You still have me. 

66
00:04:45,839 --> 00:04:47,640
 You? Forget about it. 

67
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,279
 - What's wrong with me? 
 - You guys go ahead. 

68
00:04:49,279 --> 00:04:51,179
 I'm not going. 

69
00:04:54,719 --> 00:04:58,920
 Yu Tu, are you really going to leave? 

70
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,300
 Pretty much. 

71
00:05:13,599 --> 00:05:18,580
 No matter what, I wish you a bright future. All the best. 

72
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:22,980
 All right. Let's toast. 

73
00:05:22,980 --> 00:05:26,120
 Best wishes. After this... 

74
00:05:34,879 --> 00:05:36,559
 it'll always be your treat for dinners. 

75
00:05:36,559 --> 00:05:38,159
 Yeah. 

76
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,759
 - Shall we? 
 - Sure. 
 - Okay. 

77
00:05:41,759 --> 00:05:44,220
 - Come on. 
 - Bottoms up. 

78
00:06:19,319 --> 00:06:20,840
 The door is about to close. 

79
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:24,619
 Passengers to Space City, please board quickly. 

80
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:54,700
Even Teacher Yu has a date.

81
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:58,840
While I'm all alone, playing games here. 
    

