93
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,759
Hello?

94
00:07:36,759 --> 00:07:39,060
 Are you playing Wang Zhaojun again? 

95
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:42,299
Are you spying on me?

96
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:44,879
 I just took a look. 

97
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:49,439
 Do you want to hang out with me? 

98
00:07:49,439 --> 00:07:51,480
Where are you?

99
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:06,060
You're back. Was your gathering also nearby?

100
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:07,199
Pretty much.

101
00:08:07,199 --> 00:08:10,399
They went to a karaoke, but I was not interested.

102
00:08:10,399 --> 00:08:12,500
Then where are we going?

103
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:18,040
To the movies.

104
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,260
How about this movie?

105
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:32,040
Are you doing this on purpose?

106
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:35,560
Everyone knows I'm on bad terms with the female lead.

107
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,800
I don't know much about your circle.

108
00:08:43,540 --> 00:08:45,840
What about this?

109
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,399
This movie is pretty good.

110
00:08:47,399 --> 00:08:50,120
But let me tell you that this male lead just broke up with his girlfriend,

111
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,600
who happens to be my bestie.

112
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,881
No matter how good the movie is, I can't betray my bestie.

113
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:59,560
You choose.

114
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:06,319
There is an animated film. It looks like a rerun.

115
00:09:06,997 --> 00:09:09,277
Only the seats by the aisle are left.

116
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:12,319
Put your finger here.

117
00:09:31,519 --> 00:09:34,959
We have to go quickly. It's in 15 minutes.

118
00:10:02,639 --> 00:10:04,120
Let's split up.

119
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,959
Don't look back. Someone is following us.

120
00:10:08,639 --> 00:10:10,539
Hurry up.

121
00:10:17,059 --> 00:10:19,339
 You get the tickets and go in first. 

122
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,960
 It looks like I'll have to get two tickets in one go. 

123
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,960
 How will you get in? 

124
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:30,280
 I'll tell you after you get our tickets. 

125
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:21,740
 I hope no one takes his ticket. 

126
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:25,020
 I feel like being in a spy movie rather than watching one. 

127
00:11:27,819 --> 00:11:30,479
Excuse me. Is this seat taken?

128
00:11:30,479 --> 00:11:33,899
I picked up a ticket from the counter.

129
00:11:33,899 --> 00:11:35,379
No.

130
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:14,540
   

131
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:18,679
   

132
00:12:18,679 --> 00:12:21,420
 Sometimes, I can't help but wonder 

133
00:12:21,420 --> 00:12:23,320
 what if that didn't happen to us. 

134
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:26,300
 Did he just flirt with me? 

135
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,440
 I didn't even flirt with him back. 

136
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:31,217
 I'm embarrassing myself in my entertainment circle. 

137
00:12:35,319 --> 00:12:37,120
 Maybe I didn't see it right. 

138
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,820
 What's wrong with music? 

139
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:41,260
 Nonsense! Music brought us misfortune. 

140
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,539
 - You are never to play music again. 
 - But please... 

141
00:12:43,539 --> 00:12:45,700
 - Miguel. 
 - Listen to your grandma. 

142
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:47,279
 No more music. 

143
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:48,739
 Please let me play once. 

144
00:12:48,739 --> 00:12:51,040
 This is final. 

145
00:12:51,679 --> 00:12:53,179
 Aren't you afraid you'll end up like him? 

146
00:12:53,179 --> 00:12:56,620
 No one will remember him, and he won't have a place on the altar. 

147
00:12:56,620 --> 00:13:00,059
 I don't care about being on a silly altar! 

148
00:13:00,059 --> 00:13:02,199
 - No! 
 - Mother! 

149
00:13:12,999 --> 00:13:16,820
 The major I chose at that time, my parents didn't approve of it. 

150
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:19,620
 I'm planning to give up on the galaxy. 

151
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:22,759
 What a coincidence. 

152
00:13:22,759 --> 00:13:25,999
 Won't Yu Tu feel bad watching this? 

153
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:36,750
♫  Remember me  ♫

154
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:39,390
♫  Though I have to say goodbye  ♫

155
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:42,510
♫  Remember me  ♫

156
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:45,320
♫  Don't let it make you cry  ♫

157
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:50,620
♫  For even if I'm far away, I hold you in my heart  ♫

158
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:55,530
♫  I sing a secret song to you each night we are apart  ♫

159
00:13:55,530 --> 00:13:58,430
♫  Remember me  ♫

160
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:01,600
♫  Though I have to travel far  ♫

161
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,439
I will send you home.

162
00:14:03,490 --> 00:14:07,280
♫  Each time you hear a sad guitar  ♫

163
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:12,600
♫  Know that I'm with you the only way that I can be  ♫

164
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:27,699
The movie just now, I haven't watched it before, so I didn't know the plot.

165
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:30,060
It was nice.

166
00:14:30,679 --> 00:14:34,600
The protagonist is a fortunate dreamer.

167
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:41,240
You said you wanted to give up.

168
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:44,979
Why? Is it because of your family?

169
00:14:44,979 --> 00:14:47,140
But I remember that your uncle also works in aerospace.

170
00:14:47,140 --> 00:14:49,779
Why would your parents object?

171
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:01,380
You know Peipei, she...

172
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:03,080
I know.

173
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:05,679
She has all the gossip about our class.

174
00:15:11,519 --> 00:15:14,500
Do your parents still disapprove?

175
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,740
When I went further with postgraduate study, they approved.

176
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:18,640
Then why?

177
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:33,860
A while ago... my parents came to Shanghai without informing me.

178
00:15:33,860 --> 00:15:35,860
Rather, my aunt called me

179
00:15:35,860 --> 00:15:39,899
asking about my mom's situation, saying, "Is it benign?"

180
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:43,400
 That was when I knew they were here to consult a doctor. 

181
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,960
 When I went to see them, 

182
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:49,440
 they were staying in a budget hotel. 

183
00:15:50,954 --> 00:15:55,413
 In their room, I only saw some cookies and instant noodles. 

184
00:16:02,779 --> 00:16:05,119
How's your mother now?

185
00:16:06,380 --> 00:16:10,040
She's fine. It was a false alarm.

186
00:16:13,380 --> 00:16:15,639
But I can't help but wonder.

187
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,340
If anything happens to her,

188
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:21,500
will I be able to give her the best medical treatment,

189
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,880
or have the time to be with them and care for them?

190
00:16:32,020 --> 00:16:33,820
I won't.

191
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,899
I should be able to,

192
00:16:43,799 --> 00:16:45,599
but I won't.

193
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:55,501
What will you do next?

194
00:16:55,501 --> 00:16:57,360
Work at an investment bank, maybe.

195
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:01,481
Having abandoned it for so long,

196
00:17:01,481 --> 00:17:03,879
I have to start all over again.

197
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:08,820
I have thought I was smart ever since I was a child.

198
00:17:08,820 --> 00:17:11,140
But now that I'm 30,

199
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,940
I've accomplished nothing.

200
00:17:47,380 --> 00:17:50,480
Let's go. It's late.

201
00:18:56,879 --> 00:19:00,240
 Son, we really didn't mean to hide it from you. 

202
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:04,179
 We called you, but your phone was off. 

203
00:19:04,179 --> 00:19:06,700
 Then when you called back later, 

204
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:09,530
 well... all my tension was gone. 

205
00:19:09,539 --> 00:19:12,900
 We just wanted to tell you after the results were out. 

206
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:16,660
 Besides, you were carrying out a mission. 

207
00:19:16,660 --> 00:19:19,980
 Telling you would only make you anxious for nothing, isn't that right? 

208
00:19:19,980 --> 00:19:23,740
 Besides, your father is right here with me, what's there to worry about? 

209
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:25,340
 Right? 

210
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:30,779
 The doctor said I was fine. 

211
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:37,240
 We are not going anywhere. It's pretty good here. 

212
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:40,220
 Besides, your place is too far away, it's inconvenient. 

213
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:43,500
 The doctor said I'm fine, we'll head home tomorrow. 

214
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:45,200
 She's right. 

215
00:19:45,919 --> 00:19:49,879
 Don't worry. I'm really okay. 

216
00:19:55,539 --> 00:19:58,540
 80 yuan per night, upfront. 
 (T/N: roughly $12 USD) 

217
00:20:00,660 --> 00:20:02,160
 Thanks. 

218
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:15,279
 We still have an examination report to pick up tomorrow. 

219
00:20:15,279 --> 00:20:17,479
 Don't keep telling Yu Tu. 

220
00:20:17,479 --> 00:20:20,740
 He's busy with his work. If he can't take leave to spend time with us, 

221
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:22,899
 he will feel bad. 

222
00:20:22,899 --> 00:20:28,259
 I didn't ask him to come. Why don't you believe me? 

223
00:20:29,339 --> 00:20:33,420
 Say, why do we need our son to be a high achiever? 

224
00:20:33,420 --> 00:20:38,099
 At times like this, I think that he ought to find a job in our little hometown, 

225
00:20:38,099 --> 00:20:40,579
 or dabble in finance. 

226
00:20:40,579 --> 00:20:42,980
 At least he'll have more free time. 

227
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:44,879
 You may not be a high achiever, 

228
00:20:44,879 --> 00:20:47,639
 but our son is doing so well. We should support him. 

229
00:20:47,639 --> 00:20:49,120
 Yeah, yeah. 

230
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:51,600
 Good thing I'm okay this time. 

231
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:56,100
 With the savings we have, we can't afford to overspend a penny. 

232
00:20:56,100 --> 00:21:00,460
 When Yu Tu gets married and has kids, they'll all require money. 

233
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:04,560
 He returned half of the money we gave him for the house loan down payment. 

234
00:21:04,560 --> 00:21:08,280
 I guess he doesn't have any money left with him. 

235
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:36,500
 Something came across my mind, a quote that describes you well. 

236
00:21:39,159 --> 00:21:40,759
 What is it? 

237
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:46,220
 But you are already a rabbit who has seen the most stars. 
 (T/N: comes from the Yutu robotic lunar rover that is part of Chang'e 3 mission to the moon) 

238
00:21:54,159 --> 00:21:56,299
 From Yutu's official account on Weibo? 

239
00:21:58,759 --> 00:22:00,359
 Yeah. 

240
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:15,339
 I was almost convinced by what you said. 

241
00:22:15,339 --> 00:22:17,980
 How could you say you accomplished nothing? 

242
00:22:17,980 --> 00:22:21,139
Even if you want to give up your previous career and start over,

243
00:22:21,139 --> 00:22:24,260
your past accomplishments are still there.

244
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:28,460
Although I don't know what you actually did, it must be very valuable.

245
00:22:28,460 --> 00:22:30,750
 So even if you're not doing this anymore, 

246
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:33,320
 you don't have to deny the past, right? 

247
00:22:34,079 --> 00:22:37,690
 At least you strived for your ideals. 

248
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:40,270
 This is better than you compromising when you never tried. 

249
00:22:40,279 --> 00:22:43,840
 To me at least, this is not a mistake. 

250
00:22:55,180 --> 00:22:57,879
 Do your best, Rabbit God. 

251
00:23:04,579 --> 00:23:06,279
 Thanks. 

252
00:23:06,279 --> 00:23:08,180
 You should go to bed. 

253
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:11,680
 We'll start doing ranked matches tomorrow. 

254
00:23:14,619 --> 00:23:16,419
 Good night. 

255
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:48,779
 But you are already a rabbit who has seen the most stars. 

